    {
      "parameters": {
        "operationMode": "documentLoader",
        "options": {
          "summarizationMethodAndPrompts": {
            "values": {
              "combineMapPrompt": "You are summarising one chunk of client-related data for later combination into a final staff-facing summary.\n\nYour job is to extract only the useful operational facts from the text below.\n\nRules:\n- Use only the information provided\n- Do not guess or infer facts that are not clearly stated\n- If the chunk contains little value, say so briefly\n- Keep names, dates, appointment details, notes, treatment details, invoice details, and engagement history if present\n- Ignore filler, repetition, raw formatting noise, IDs unless operationally useful, and empty fields\n- Use concise Australian English\n- Output short bullet points only\n- Focus on facts that would help staff understand the client before an appointment\n\nText:\n\"{text}\"\n\nReturn:\n- Key facts from this chunk\n- Important dates\n- Any risks, concerns, or follow-up indicators\n- If nothing meaningful is present, output: No useful operational data in this chunk.",
              "prompt": "You are combining multiple partial summaries about one client into a single clear staff-facing summary.\n\nYour task is to produce a concise pre-appointment summary that staff can read quickly.\n\nRules:\n- Use only the information provided in the partial summaries\n- Do not invent missing facts\n- If something is unknown, say Unknown\n- Remove duplicates\n- Prefer the most specific and useful detail\n- Keep the tone practical, direct, and operational\n- Use concise Australian English\n- Make the output easy to scan\n\nPartial summaries:\n\"{text}\"\n\nCreate the final response using exactly these sections:\n\nClient Snapshot\n- Customer code / client identifier\n- Clinic\n- Status\n- Any key profile details\n\nLast Appointment\n- Date\n- Outcome\n- Key service or treatment details\n\nUpcoming Appointment\n- Date\n- Purpose if known\n\nEngagement History\n- Lead source\n- Contact behaviour\n- Attendance / follow-up patterns\n\nNotes Summary\n- Key notes relevant to staff\n- Preferences or concerns\n\nTreatment / Service History\n- Current or previous treatments/services\n- Progress indicators if known\n\nFinancial / Commercial Indicators\n- Packages\n- Invoice activity\n- Repeat business indicators\n\nRisks / Concerns\n- Gaps in attendance\n- Follow-up risk\n- Missing or conflicting information\n\nSuggested Next Action\n- 1 to 3 short practical actions staff should take\n\nRequirements:\n- Use bullet points under each section\n- Keep it concise\n- Show dates clearly\n- If a section has no data, write Unknown"
            }
          }
        }
      },
